From: Elvir Crncevic
Subject: fix: suppress stop string matching inside reasoning/thinking blocks

Stop sequences (e.g. "Question:" from lm_eval) were being matched against
tokens inside <think>...</think> blocks, killing generation before any
content was produced. This caused ~8.6% empty responses in P/D mode with
Nemotron 3 Ultra on GSM8K.

The detokenizer's check_stop_strings() operates on the raw output text
which includes reasoning tokens. The reasoning parser that splits
<think> from content runs in the serving layer, after generation is
already terminated. This patch bridges the gap by passing reasoning
markers (start/end token strings) from the serving layer down to the
detokenizer, which tracks whether generation is inside a thinking block
and suppresses stop string matching while it is.

Files changed:
  vllm/v1/engine/__init__.py                           - Add reasoning_markers field to EngineCoreRequest
  vllm/v1/engine/detokenizer.py                        - Track <think> state, skip stop checks in reasoning
  vllm/v1/engine/async_llm.py                          - Thread reasoning_markers through generate()/add_request()
  vllm/entrypoints/openai/chat_completion/serving.py   - Pass reasoning parser markers into generate()

